    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI've run into some strange bug recently (since neovim 0.9.0). The bug is that when I enter the command line **too quickly** right after the vim startup (before UI is fully load yet), the statusline and winbar is gone and shown in black -- it does not display anything.\r\n\r\nSee the screencast:\r\n\r\n![winbar-bug](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1009873/236751492-3298c496-b19a-4b65-be79-7646b19215ae.gif)\r\n\r\nWhen I press `:` as soon as I enter `nvim` in the shell, neovim enters the cmdline before the UI fully draws. And then the statusline and winbar are broken.\r\n\r\n- This happens only when Both of `winbar` and `set lazyredraw` is set.\r\n- When either `set nolazyredraw` or `winbar == \"\"`, it works fine.\r\n\r\nNote: Even if I do `:mode` (redraw everything), it doesn't get fixed.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nrepro.vim\r\n```vim\r\nset statusline=%1*%{winnr()}\\ %*%<\\ %f\\ %h%m%r%=%l,%c%V\\ (%P)\r\nset lazyredraw\r\nlua vim.opt.winbar = \"(winbar)\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n`$ nvim -u repro.vim`\r\n\r\nTry to press `:` as soon and quickly as possible.\r\n\r\n![23534 reproduction](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1009873/236752664-8231b1a8-77ef-4618-8a90-283f2b73b1fd.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nEven when we enter the command line too quickly, the UI should not break.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-4317+g13e7e4e67-Homebrew, v0.9.0, v0.8.3 (stable)\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNO, vim works fine. Actually not applicable because winbar doesn't exist in vim (9.0.1486)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS, linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nHomebrew",
    "closed_at": "2023-05-08T08:25:04Z",
    "comment_data": [
